  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.jallcom.2003.09.015.pdf_1_36",
    "text": "A further new compound was found in the as-cast samples containing 16.6 at.% Er. The X-ray powder pattern of this compound was very similar to the powder pattern of the ErNiB boride. The crystal structure of the new Ero.917Ni4.09B boride was determined using an X-ray single-crystal method: space group P6/mmm; a = 1.48399 nm; c = 0.69194 nm [15]. This structure is very similar to the Yo.915Ni4.12B structure [16]. The Ero.917Ni4.09B boride decomposes after annealing, and the main phase is the ErNi4B compound.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
